I will rise & shine,
have a worthy sign,
get brighter than sunshine,
………………………….. ???

I used to be that under confident kid:

- who used to doubt himself 10 times before even asking a question in a class
- my teachers used to make fun of me
- my classmates used to laugh at the way I used to try to copy american dialogues because I didn’t know how to speak in english properly.

and that was the time I started watching videos of people like gary vee, richard branson etc. and that would only fill me with disappointment that ‘it’s not possible for us common people to have a dream life, I don’t think I have it in me’. 

and then one day I gave a class presentation in front of 40 students, received a standing ovation and that filled me with confidence that hey! it’s not that difficult, since then everything in life has been about just one presentation, one speech, one moment, one step at a time. 

we all look at farfetch dreams and think it’s only for few lucky people, but guess what it’s for everyone who goes for it.

nothing was handed to me in the speaking world, didn’t know how to speak properly forget inspiring people, but I focused on 40 students in front of me, focused on only 100 people who follow me on social media and here we are today 8 years later.

if you focus on what’s in front of you and give your 100% in this one moment, every dream is possible, everything is achievable.

Comment: What are your dreams? (so that we all can help each other in building them)

‘Figuring Out’ is a habit, it’s a feeling that I want everyone to feel proud of.

I am a person who is driven by emotions, everything I do is from a space of love, inspiration, freedom, drive, and hunger.

And since the last few years, I started spreading that at large with all of you,
it’s great to build businesses out of systems but as a person, we all should be driven out of emotions, not processes, because when you share those emotions with people, they support, they cheer and they join you in the journey.

This year my top 3 dreams were to:
- Start a clothing brand and spread the feeling of figuring out
- publish a book
- build a festival

-> First dream ✅ 
-> Second Dream - (Launching my book in November 🤫) *get ready* 🚀
-> Third Dream - This couldn’t happen this year but will make sure we achieve it next year.

Comment: *Let’s do it*
(If you want me to share everything and if you are ready to help me with ideas and your learnings.)

Raj Shamani 3.0 begins

I am so nervous, scared, and confused yet excited about what’s going to be next for us. We talk a lot about business and startups on our channel but now that I am building a new startup ‘lag gaye hai bro’ 😝 you don’t know at any point what’s going to happen but that’s the beauty. And that’s why I want to come up front and show you the entire journey of my startup from Day 0,
- how did I figure out the idea?
- how do I raise funds?
- how am I building the team?
- how am I making money and scaling the business? everything.

Because one day India is going to be the best economy in the world and we need thousands of entrepreneurs to build our nation but if we all make the same mistakes it will take us centuries, so why not I share every mistake I make and every strategy that works for me with you guys and you guys share that with me in the comments, then we all can learn from each other and grow faster by learning from each other’s mistakes/failures.
